The police yesterday arraigned a 54-year-old driver, Kehinde Julius, at an Ebute Meta Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly stealing 3180 litres of diesel valued at N859,000. Julius was charged with three counts of conspiracy, conduct in a manner likely to cause breach of the peace and stealing. Prosecuting Inspector Kehinde Omisakin said the defendant committed the offence on February 2, at 10, Abebe Village, Iganmu, Lagos. He alleged that the defendant stole 3,180 litres of diesel worth N858,000 from a truck belonging to Lanre Ayibiowu. The defendant pleaded not guilty. Chief Magistrate A.O. Komolafe admitted the defendant to N500,000 bail with two sureties each in the like sum, who must have proof of tax payment. The case continues on April 9.